data.text:
Synopsis[]

Similar to its predecessor Super Cars, Classic Cars entails an hour's worth of the world's most sought-after classic cars, including behind-the-wheel views of the Daimler Dart, the Jaguars E-Type and MKII, the Triumph Stag, Ferrari Dino, Gordon Keeble, MG B, Facel Vega, and AC Cobra 427.

Most footage is presumably from Series 24 - Series 29 of original format Top Gear, as was the case with its predecessor, although it is possible the Cobra footage is from even earlier, as William Woollard and Beki Adam reviewed the car for Series 21.
